# AI Dev OS Layer Dependency Check

When editing L1 (philosophy) or L2 (principles/decision-criteria) files, enforce the dependency rule.

## Rules

### L1 Philosophy Files
- MUST NOT contain tool-specific terms: "Claude Code", "Cursor", "Kiro", "Copilot", etc.
- MUST NOT contain framework-specific terms: "Next.js", "FastAPI", "React", etc.
- MUST remain abstract and timeless (lifespan: 2-5 years)

### L2 Principles / Decision Criteria Files
- MUST NOT contain framework-specific implementation details
- MUST NOT reference specific library APIs
- MAY reference general paradigms (OOP, FP, etc.)
- MUST remain at the principle level (lifespan: 1-3 years)

## When Violations Are Found
Warn the user:
- Explain which term violates the dependency rule
- Suggest moving the detail to L3 (guidelines) or L4 (AI frames)
- Quote the dependency rule: "Upper layers never reference lower layers"

## Language

Respond in the same language as the project's .cursorrules file.
